						<summary>

						<p>Right niche in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> of the Mahādēva temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">12th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged fragment record states that Chinni seṭṭi and Bāchaṇa, sons of Hammikabbe and disciple of Tribhuvanasēna Siddhā[nta]dēva got the image of the goddess (name lost) made. [No. 223/A.R. No. 767 above].</p>						

						<p>It is in characters of the 12th century A.D. </p>						

						</summary>
